          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>1 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: KFQ 39B; Lines per page: 7; Dimensions: 120 x 180 mm; Qurʾānic Text: Q 51:7-9; Script style: kūfī D; Estimated date of production: 800-1000.</p>
              <p>Cf. entry by François Déroche about fragment KFQ 39B (Déroche, <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, p. 107): "54 / Single folio / 9th or 10th century AD / 12x18cm, with 7 lines to the page / <hi rend="italic">Material</hi> Parchment; the verso is the hair side / <hi rend="italic">Text area</hi> 6x12.5cm / <hi rend="italic">Script</hi> A variant of group D / <hi rend="italic">Accession no</hi>. KFQ 39B / This folio contains <hi rend="italic">Sūrat al-dhāriyāt</hi> (LI), verses 7-16. The text is written in dark brown ink, with diacritical strokes added in ink or in colour. Red dots indicate the vocalization. The verses are not divided. The folio has been stained and there is a hole in its upper part.”</p>
              <p><ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/1039/page/1r?sura=31&amp;verse=16">KFQ 39A</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/1040/page/1r?sura=51&amp;verse=7">KFQ 39B</ref> are similar in script style but belong two distinct codices. </p>
            </summary>
